               <msContents>
                  <summary> A copy of the <title>Bahār-i Dānish</title> (Spring of Wisdom) by
                        <persName key="person_17950016" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/17950016/">ʻInāyat
                        Allāh (d. ca. 1671)</persName>, relates the romantic adventures of Jahāndār
                     Sulṭān and Bahravar Bānū, which serves as a frame story interwoven with other
                     tales. One of six copies held in the Rylands, this redaction features the
                     preface by the author's younger brother and pupil <persName
                        key="person_270970434">Muḥammad Ṣāliḥ</persName> followed by his own
                     introduction in which he explains how he adapted the tale from one that he
                     heard a young Brahmin recite. </summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_991-item1">
                     <author key="person_17950016" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/17950016/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">ʻInāyat Allāh, d. ca.
                           1671</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">‘Ināyat Allāh Kanbū
                           Lāhūrī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Kanbū, ‘Ināyat
                        Allāh</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">عنايت الله</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">عنايت الله كنبو لاهوری</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">كنبو، عنايت الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1151">Bahār-i Dānish</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1151">بهار دانش</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> فاتحه کتاب مستطاب افرینش و پیرایهٔ صحیفهٔ دانش و بینش حمد
                        خداوند خردبخش سخن آفرین و صورت نمای معنی ایجاد و تکوین است که بر لطایف ابداع
                        و صنایع اختراع قدرت کامله پس از ماهتاب... </incipit>
                     <!-- <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="209a" to="209a"> برگ ۲۰۹ر (folio 209a):</locus> سیه کاری مکن
                        چون خامهٔ خویش * بشو از چشم بر خون نامه‌ٔ خویش | زبان را گوشمالی خاموشی ده *
                        که هست از هرچه کوئی خاموشی به. </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="233a" to="233a"> برگ ۲۳۳ر (folio 233a):</locus> تم بالخیر کتبه
                        العبد الفقیر محمد کاتب اللاری سنة ثمان وثلاثين وتسعماية</colophon> -->

                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>S. H. Qasemi documents 244 manuscripts and printed editions of this work.
                        C. A. Storey also notes various manuscripts and translations into English,
                        German, French, Turkish, and Urdu. For other copies of this work held in the
                        Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7392"><idno>Persian
                              MS 88</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6678">199</ref>,
